---

<IndividualPageLayout
    title={seoTitle}
    description={seoDescription}
    schema={pageSchema}
    pageTitle={pageTitle}
    heroImage="/oscar/media/die-casting-investment-casting-forging-cnc-high-precision-machining-title-bar-2.jpg"
    heroImageAlt="Forged Inconel 718 rings and high-performance industrial components"
    faqSectionTitle="Frequently Asked Questions: A356 Aluminum"
    faqItems={faqs}
    ctaTitle="Request Quote For A356 Aluminum Casting"
    ctaDescription=""
    sourcesTitle="Sources"
    sourcesList={sources}
    resourcesTitle="Our Internal Resources for Die Casting, Investment casting, Forging and Sand Casting"
    resourcesList={internalResources}
>

    <div slot="full-width" class="individual-content">

        <section id="overview">
            <div class="content-container">
                
                <h2>A356 Aluminum Casting & T6 Heat Treatment: Precision Lightweight Manufacturing</h2>

                <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:items-center mt-6">
                    <div>
                        <p>
                            ForceBeyond is a premier manufacturing partner specializing in superior-quality A356 aluminum casting components. Engineered for the most demanding environments, A356 aluminum offers an exceptional combination of lightweight design, high strength, and excellent castability for intricate, complex geometries.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            With highly scalable production capabilities—ranging from low-volume runs of a few dozen pieces to high-volume production of thousands—we produce A356 castings weighing anywhere from a few ounces to over 200 pounds. From automotive and aerospace to fluid control and heavy machinery, ForceBeyond delivers fully finished, pressure-tight A356 components ready for critical assemblies.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="relative">
                        <div class="overflow-hidden">
                            <img
                                src="/oscar/media/a356-aluminum-cast-finned-fan-clutch-housing-4k.webp"
                                alt="A356 aluminum cast finned fan clutch housing with a machined mounting flange and radial cooling fins on a white background."
                                class="w-full h-auto object-cover hover:scale-105 transition-transform duration-500"
                            />
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="technical-specifications">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Technical Specifications: A356 Alloy Properties</h2>
                <p>
                    A356 is a highly versatile 7% Silicon and 0.3% Magnesium alloy. It is widely considered the logical choice for complex castings that require excellent pressure tightness, weldability, and corrosion resistance. It is frequently utilized as a cast substitute for wrought aluminum alloy 6061.
                </p>

                <h3 class="mt-8 mb-4">Chemical Composition (A356)</h3>
                <p>
                    ForceBeyond ensures strict adherence to metallurgical standards to prevent impurities and maximize castability.
                </p>
                <div class="content-table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="col">Element</th>
                                <th scope="col">Percentage (%)</th>
                                <th scope="col">Element</th>
                                <th scope="col">Percentage (%)</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Silicon (Si)</th>
                                <td>7.0</td>
                                <th scope="row">Iron (Fe)</th>
                                <td>0.20 (Max)</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Magnesium (Mg)</th>
                                <td>0.3</td>
                                <th scope="row">Zinc (Zn)</th>
                                <td>0.10 (Max)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3 class="mt-8 mb-4">Mechanical Properties (A356-T6 Condition)</h3>
                <p>
                    To maximize the alloy's structural integrity, A356 is almost universally supplied in the T5 or T6 heat-treated condition.
                </p>
                <div class="content-table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="col">Mechanical Property</th>
                                <th scope="col">Value (T6 Condition)</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Ultimate Tensile Strength</th>
                                <td>33 ksi</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Yield Strength</th>
                                <td>24 ksi</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Shearing Strength</th>
                                <td>26 ksi</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <th scope="row">Brinell Hardness (500 kg)</th>
                                <td>70 HB</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="heat-treatment">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>The A356-T6 Heat Treatment Process</h2>
                <p>
                    To achieve the "excellent" mechanical rating required for mission-critical applications, ForceBeyond utilizes a specialized, highly controlled T6 Heat Treatment Process. This two-step thermal process dramatically increases the hardness and yield strength of the raw casting.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Solution Heat Treating & Quenching:</strong> After the A356 castings cool naturally, they are placed into high-temperature ovens for a set duration to dissolve alloying elements into a solid solution. The parts are then rapidly quenched to freeze these elements in place.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Artificial Aging:</strong> In the second step, the castings are moved to low-temperature ovens. This controlled aging precipitates the alloying elements, locking the grain structure and resulting in a massive increase in the metal's final hardness and mechanical strength.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="why-partner">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Why Partner with ForceBeyond for A356 Casting?</h2>
                <p>
                    Procuring high-strength aluminum castings requires a partner with deep metallurgical expertise and advanced process control.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Exceptional Fluidity for Intricate Designs:</strong> A356's high silicon content gives it superior castability, allowing ForceBeyond to accurately cast highly intricate, thin-walled designs that are pressure-tight and resistant to hot cracking.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Broad Weight Capacity:</strong> Unlike many foundries limited to small parts, our scalable infrastructure can seamlessly cast A356 components ranging from lightweight ounces up to heavy-duty, 200+ pound structural parts.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Superior Weldability & Corrosion Resistance:</strong> A356 inherently resists corrosive environments, making it ideal for marine (submarine), petrochemical, and outdoor agricultural applications.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="tier-1-5-integration">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Tier-1.5 Integration: Precision Cast-to-Machine Solutions</h2>
                <p>
                    ForceBeyond operates on a Tier-1.5 model. We do not just pour metal; we deliver finished, assembly-ready components. By integrating our casting operations with advanced secondary processing under one ISO 9001:2015 certified quality system, we eliminate supply chain bottlenecks.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Our In-House Secondary Operations Include:</strong>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>High-Precision CNC Machining:</strong> 5-axis milling, drilling, and tapping for ultra-tight tolerances.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Protective & Aesthetic Coatings:</strong> E-coating, anodizing (ideal for aluminum), powder coating, and chrome plating.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Surface Preparation:</strong> Sanding, shot blasting, and painting.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="certified-applications">
            <div class="content-container">
                <h2>Certified A356-T6 Casting Applications</h2>
                <p>
                    Because of its high strength-to-weight ratio and pressure tightness, ForceBeyond supplies A356-T6 castings to the world's most demanding sectors:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Aerospace & Defense:</strong> High-strength air-frame structural components and space-frame parts.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Automotive & Transportation:</strong> Transmission cases, oil pans, truck chassis parts, and flywheel castings.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>HVAC & Fluid Control:</strong> High-velocity blowers, impellers, and heavy-duty pump bodies/housings.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Industrial Machinery:</strong> High-strength machine components requiring exceptional dimensional stability.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
</IndividualPageLayout>